<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ881020-0154 </DOCNO><HL> PPG to Expand U.K. Plant </HL><SO> </SO><CO> PPG </CO><DATELINE> PITTSBURGH  </DATELINE><TEXT>   PPG Industries Inc., which makes glass, chemicals, coatings and medical instruments, said its board approved installing a second furnace to produce glass fiber for both reinforcement and textile applications at a cost of more than $75 million at its plant at Wigan, England.    The furnace is expected to be completed by the fall of 1990, the company said. It will triple the plant's capacity and add capability to produce textile yarns. </TEXT></DOC>